Activity 1.1.1: Working with ICIMOD and government partners at both national and district-levels, review existing survey results and High Resolution Satellite Imagery (Digital Global, NASA,.SERVIR) of identified district to determine areas and communities where threat and interventions are most critical,

Activity 1.1.2: Development of user-friendly Hazard Mapping and Vulnerability Analysis (HVMA) Tool Kit which incorporates concepts of the Geo-Design Approach prioritization of communities  where preparedness and mitigation activities are most required – with particular focus on local agriculture context,

Activity 1.1.3: In prioritized communities, conduct on-the-ground AHVMA to identify critical landslides-affected and prone areas, which impact on  agricultural production and irrigation infrastructure – using simple, yet scientifically informed tools,

Activity 1.1.4: Review and/or establish comprehensive watershed management plans through a community-based integrated livelihoods.

 Activity 1.2.1: Working with the Department of Soil Conservation and Watershed Management, implement a campaign to seal off smaller land cracks in order to avoid water infiltration and expansion.

Activity 1.2.2: Stabilize the prioritized landslides with a combination of bioengineering techniques (plantations, bamboo, ground cover, etc.) and engineering structures (gabion walls, check dams, etc.)

Activity 1.2.3: Provide training in contingency planning to community members within existing cooperatives, Watershed Management Committees or Forest User Groups.

Activity 1.2.4: Work with MOAD, provide training to farmer organizations and cooperatives on improved technologies for agro-forestry, slope stabilization and soil conservation.

 Activity 2.1.1: Provide key leaders from MOAD and MOFSC at both national and district levels (DADO, DSCO) with tools, protocols and training for identifying landslide affected prone agricultural areas;

 

Activity 2.1.2: Working with partners of the Landslide Sub-Groups for Mitigation and Capacity Building, test and refine community-based mitigation and rehabilitation strategies and technologies in coordination with existing government partners to promote scale-up and replication to further districts;

Activity 2.1.3: Lessons learnt and best practice documents are created and shared through stakeholder dissemination events and used to advocate for continued budget support for the maintenance and operation of established systems;

Activity 2.1.4: Conduct work shop for the incorporation of best practices and strategies into development programming at the relevant ministries;
